Mar 29 2007	Great hotel	We recently stayed at 51 Buckingham Gate for 2 nights with my children. It was a fantastic location with a beautiful courtyard and great service. The tube (St. James) is just steps away and Victoria is a 5 min walk. The hotel had DVD's to borrow which was convenient for the kids at night and the service was very very good. There were a few negatives: many of the doors don't stay open or shut and this becomes very irritating after a while. For example the kitchen door was held open by a waste bin. It seems trivial but it really gets to you after a while; the rooms are also too crowded with furnishings, in particular the bedrooms so you can almost not move; we had a 2 bedroom which would have been great but we needed twin beds in the 2nd bedroom and it only had a queen so I suggest you check to make sure you're getting the configuration you want before you book. There are many positives: The apartment comes fully stocked with tea and coffee and milk which was fantastic. We went around the corner to Sainsburys and picked up ready made meals for the kids which was great and a bargain by London standards. We also ate in the restaurant next door (part of the hotel) and it was superb. They had a special for 16pounds which was very good and reasonable value. We also ate in the Indian restarurant attached to the hotel and it was one of the best Indian restaurants I have ever eaten in. One word of caution on the apartment: there is a 110v plug in the living room and it blew up my hair straightener so be careful. they did refund me for it, however. Everything else was perfect.	
